race.description: Ladbrokes Spring Hosted Pots Mdn Plate
race.comment: KATSUMI OROCHI (5) resumes having run a bolter at big odds in the G3 Blue Diamond Prelude, sticking on for third, beaten just 2.5 lengths and not far off subsequent Blue Diamond winner Devil Night. Now with the Freedman yard, he comes back off a fairly long break but anything like his debut will take beating. SOUTHERN SLAMMER (1) resumes. He was well beaten on debut when in the market at Geelong but has jumped out well leading in for the new yard and can be a quick improver. COOLY (9) went well on debut two-and-a-half weeks ago when fourth over 1110m at Kilmore. Fitter and can't be ignored. PRESTIGE ZERPRISE (7) unraced 3yo colt who has trialled five times. Best trial form was when he won at Caulfield Heath on October 8. In the mix.
